The paper discusses a learning rule for decision-making problems that involve combining decision-makers with limited information-processing capabilities. This is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the learning rule in reinforcement learning and adaptive control, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on information-theoretic principles and bounded rationality suggests that it may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
